$Id$
------------------------------------------------------------

xindy (`fleXible INDexing sYstem') is a flexible index-processor. See
the files in directory ./Doc for a detailed description of what xindy
does.

This directory contains the distribution as of July 1996. It is
organized as follows:

  Doc/		contains a manual in html,dvi,ps,info,txt-formats

  bin/          several scripts and tools forming the enviroment of xindy

  modules/	the library of pre-defined indexstyle-modules

  binaries/     some binaries separated into machine-depended
	        subdirectories

  src/          the source of the xindy-system

  tests/        contains a complete testsuite

  contrib/	contains additional programs that can be used to make
		xindy work with various document-formatting systems


This distribution is also available at

	ftp://ftp.th-darmstadt.de/pub/tex/src/xindy/

or at our homepage at

	http://www.iti.informatik.th-darmstadt.de/@@@ (not availabe yet!)

which contains the most up-to-date information about xindy.

Currently we support binary-distributions for the following platforms:

    Linux ELF        i386
    AIX-3.2          rs6000
    HP-UX 9.x        hppa
    SunOS 5.2-4      sun4m
    IRIX 5.3	     mips

Everybody is encouraged to port xindy to new platforms. For any kind
of suggestions, helpful comments, questions, bug reports and such,
please mail to the xindy mailing-list

	xindy@iti.informatik.th-darmstadt.de

You can subscribe to the list by sending a mail to

	xindy-approval@iti.informatik.th-darmstadt.de

with the subject `SUBSCRIBE xindy'.


See file INSTALL for a description how to install this distribution.


